test(iter24): real cTrader e2e scenario tests + richer harness trade rows

With EngineHostFactory.Create unblocked (iter24-p9), the cTrader pipeline runs
end-to-end again. Adds CtraderScenarioTests (real engine <-> NetMQ <-> cBot in
cTrader's backtester, live data; skips without creds):
- HappyPath_EurUsd_TradeLedgerHasIntegrity — entry prices valid, lots positive,
  SL/TP closes have real exit prices.
- EdgeCase_WeekendRange — sparse Sat/Sun range: completes cleanly, 0 bars -> 0
  trades (no invented trades). Verified: 9 bars, 0 trades.
- AfterRun_NoOrphanCtraderProcesses — CLI fully reaped, no orphans.

Extends CtraderTestHarness.Result with TradeRow[] (symbol/dir/lots/entry/exit/
net/commission/swap/exitReason) so scenarios can assert on the trade ledger, not
just bar counts.

All 3 pass against real cTrader (~28s each). Surfaced a real finding (handled
separately): engine-requested closes report PnL=0 and all exits read FORCE.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
